response.original_title: Fight Club Pro Project Mayhem VIII Night Two
response.overview: The rules saw participants enter in staggered intervals, with the last person due to enter being Wolverhampton’s Trent Seven. However the WWE superstar never made it to the ring, ultimately being thrown off the entrance stage and through a table.  Fight Club: PRO wouldn’t be disadvantaged for long, with Jimmy Havoc making yet another surprise appearance at Project Mayhem, to aid the promotion.  Birmingham’s Dan Moloney would ultimately secure the pinfall for Fight Club: PRO, piledriving Kyle Fletcher through a table.
response.title: Fight Club Pro Project Mayhem VIII Night Two
